97
00:04:57,598 --> 00:05:00,801 line:-2
She always checks the bus schedule
before starting the workout,


98
00:05:00,868 --> 00:05:03,837 line:-2
and she uses the Mission Gym app
to track her exercise.


99
00:05:03,904 --> 00:05:06,874 line:-2
This is where Shortcuts
is bound to come in handy.


100
00:05:07,641 --> 00:05:11,645 line:-2
She can set up a Shortcut automation
that will run when she arrives at the gym.


101
00:05:11,712 --> 00:05:12,980 line:-1
So when she gets there,


102
00:05:13,046 --> 00:05:16,083 line:-2
she can see the bus schedule
and start her workout.


103
00:05:16,583 --> 00:05:19,386 line:-2
So, as you can see
through this user's journey,


104
00:05:19,453 --> 00:05:22,589 line:-2
system intelligence
can help people discover new apps


105
00:05:22,656 --> 00:05:25,959 line:-2
and accelerate them every step of the way
after that.


106
00:05:27,361 --> 00:05:29,897 line:-2
By leveraging
these intelligence touch points,


107
00:05:29,963 --> 00:05:31,665 line:-1
